1783564952292491	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqhQ		item.create	bn-2cvx	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 4: merging bn-b2r auto-rebased sibling bn-3ps \"2 commit(s) replayed\" — textually clean, semantically broken (sibling's tests used an API the merge had just reworked). Nothing suggested re-validating.\n\nCHANGE: when sibling auto-rebase replays a sibling over the new epoch, compute the intersection of (paths touched by the epoch range rebased over) and (paths the sibling workspace touches). Machinery exists: ff_absorb::evaluate_ff_safety does touched-path intersection; ws overlap computes ws-vs-ws overlap; auto_rebase already knows old_epoch/new_epoch. If the intersection is non-empty:\n1. Append to the merge-output sibling line (auto_rebase.rs describe / merge.rs:4483-4510): \"replayed over commits touching N file(s) your workspace also touches — re-run your tests before merging\".\n2. Include the same hint + the file list (capped, e.g. first 5) in the bn-1abp auto-rebase-notice.json (auto_rebase.rs record_rebase_notice :332-372) so the sibling owner sees it on next maw exec (sync/notice.rs render).\n\nDECLINED for now (noted in bn-38nz): per-workspace postsync hook (e.g. cargo test after sync) — real feature, separate proposal if demand recurs.\nTests: hint appears when overlap non-empty, absent when disjoint; notice JSON carries the file list.","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"s","title":"Auto-rebase overlap hint: flag semantic risk when replayed commits touch files the sibling also touches"}	blake3:fQaqZSPbZ467pgnrXxzwik71GNiRm6LuKNMDSpOj2To
1783564952292759	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqxQ		item.link	bn-38nz	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-2cvx"}	blake3:BY2mXifqPCuGyVsp3icfsuKh0s4GGPtGVlB6faatwm8
1783564966326064	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrBQ		item.create	bn-3eew	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 5. Investigation: the requested auto-sync ALREADY EXISTS — real merges auto-absorb strict-FF trunk commits (bn-11ip: reconcile_epoch_with_branch merge.rs:2982-3144, gated by merge.auto_absorb_ff default TRUE; safety = strict FF + no in-flight ws touched-path intersection), and maw doctor --repair does the same via epoch_drift::auto_advance_if_safe. The ONLY gap: ws merge --check is a read-only dry run and re-prints \"trunk has N commit(s) not made through maw; the epoch is behind\" (merge.rs:1770) on every check until something absorbs it. That NOTE trains users to ignore warnings.\n\nDESIGN DECISION (lead): --check stays strictly non-mutating. Fix is wording only:\n1. In output_check_result, classify drift with epoch_drift::classify_drift (or reuse trunk_commits_ahead_of_epoch + evaluate_ff_safety). When FF-and-safe: downgrade to informational, e.g. \"trunk is N commit(s) ahead of the epoch (will be absorbed automatically when you merge)\". No \"To reconcile first\" scolding.\n2. When FF but BLOCKED (touched-path intersection) or truly diverged: keep a real warning and point at maw epoch sync / maw doctor --repair.\n3. JSON check output should carry the drift classification.\nTests: both wordings; json field.","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"xs","title":"merge --check epoch-behind NOTE: informational when FF-auto-absorbable, warning only on real divergence"}	blake3:pxmAM9FZg4FpZQVRGPv3ZmP_I1ipAVSqeXjyFL6WvyU
1783564966326305	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrRQ		item.link	bn-38nz	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-3eew"}	blake3:XcQ7SwT2DcoHbPv0A5tnftvlXaPYsN5J_71U8evX46g
1783564973362965	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrhQ		item.create	bn-1aey	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 6: merge --destroy run from a shell cwd inside the destroyed workspace; every chained command afterwards failed with opaque errors (ensure_repo_root -> std::env::current_dir \"Could not determine current directory\").\n\nCHANGE: in both destroy paths — workspace::create::destroy() (create.rs:689-900) and handle_post_merge_destroy() (merge.rs:5677-5760, which already computes canonical_ws per workspace in its C4 root-guard :5717-5745) — capture and canonicalize the process cwd BEFORE deletion (after deletion current_dir may already fail) and, if it is inside a workspace being destroyed, print one stderr line: \"note: your current directory is inside workspace '<name>' which was just destroyed — cd back to the project root before running more commands.\" Do not block the destroy.\nAlso: ensure_repo_root's current_dir() failure context (workspace/mod.rs:1943-1967) could hint \"(was your directory deleted, e.g. by a workspace destroy? cd to the project root)\". Cheap, worth adding.\nTests: unit-level check on the path-containment helper; destroy from inside prints the note (integration if feasible).","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"xs","title":"Warn when the invoking shell's cwd is inside a workspace being destroyed"}	blake3:XEL52aHfR-3emD8GjpgtYT6zEYpS62-j8Zc-Nq4rbEY
