1783564981516120	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysBQ		item.create	bn-1kop	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 7. Investigation: ws merge and ws list ALREADY have --format json (workspace/mod.rs:1123-1134 with MergeSuccessOutput merge.rs:166-187; list at workspace/mod.rs:639-661) — the reporter missed it. ws sync --format json is being added in bn-mq6j. Remaining gaps:\n\n1. SENTINEL: merge text-mode success ends with \"Merged to {branch}: {msg} from {ws...}\" + push hint (merge.rs:4663-4677) — no grep-stable token, and it interpolates the free-text commit message. Add a final stable line consistent with --check's convention: \"[OK] merged <ws1>[, <ws2>...] into <branch> @ <short-sha>\". Keep existing lines above it.\n2. ws list --help: the lifecycle vocabulary lives only in code (LifecycleState, lifecycle.rs:37-176, kebab-case slugs; free-text annotations composed in list.rs:330-349 and text_annotation :465-499 with [lifecycle:<slug>] tags). Add the vocabulary table to the List clap doc comment (workspace/mod.rs:618-623): each state slug + meaning + fix_command hint. Keep it terse (agents read --help).\n3. While there: mention --format json in the ws merge/ws list help text if not already prominent, since a fresh field report missed its existence — discoverability failure.\nTests: sentinel line format asserted in an existing merge integration test; help text contains the state slugs.","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"s","title":"Merge output: stable [OK] sentinel line; document lifecycle label vocabulary in ws list --help"}	blake3:lxjfO0ollG3aeBMkIUI0SuvpCvHCy3M-3oF7CFRdhrM
