1783565467748147	w-1aey	itc:v3:AWLOSZP5M5JJMlAAAAAAQd1a_rdVWoAAAAExAw		item.comment	bn-1aey	{"body":"Implemented: shared containment helper cwd_is_inside()/path_is_within() in workspace/mod.rs; wired into create.rs destroy() and merge.rs handle_post_merge_destroy() (captured BEFORE deletion, one stderr note printed after destroy completes); ensure_repo_root's current_dir() error context now hints at workspace-destroy-deleted-cwd. Added 5 unit tests for path_is_within (child/equal/sibling/parent/symlink) + 4 integration tests in tests/destroy_cwd_warning_bn_1aey.rs (standalone destroy force/clean from inside, from-outside negative, merge --destroy from inside source). cargo fmt + clippy clean. Running full just check next."}	blake3:gs_4Gte-iabI27Qydlip_osA2vjwDZJCu4eY11tzRnY
1783565656247854	w-1xmk	itc:v3:AWKZOSSSZJJJkkmcQAAAQbXVVaqrVW4AAAE4Aw		item.comment	bn-1xmk	{"body":"Investigation complete. Plan: (1) working_copy.rs replay_snapshot_with_merge_protection — broaden 'overlapping' to include any dirty stash path whose committed content changed between anchor_epoch and epoch_after (not just resolved_paths), so merge=union journals get driver-aware 3-way instead of bare stash_apply (mode b). (2) update_default_workspace — capture in-memory pre-merge dirty bytes after anchor, pin a DURABLE recovery ref (refs/manifold/recovery/<ws>/<ts>) from the snapshot oid, always route through merge-protection replay, then post-replay fidelity verify+repair for committed-unchanged files with loud recover warning. (3) snapshot_working_copy — stash-None-despite-dirty becomes Err (mirror bn-3mpx) with safe in-memory repair fallback. (4) merge --check surfaces dirty trunk files (informational). recover.rs already lists pinned recovery/ refs as 'pinned' rows, so no recover change needed. Tests in tests/bn_1xmk_*.rs."}	blake3:pXmWbAtqDQEZj94jk9T1iq7qfVLPRSvScJatdQnPMoQ
