1783620673604274	w-3rst	itc:v3:AWKZJPyZnmZnNAAAAAAAQbVfrb227AAAAAEuAg		item.assign	bn-3rst	{"action":"assign","agent":"w-3rst"}	blake3:LbCQERv67K_-9tO9GeiEtapmmqo5Cq91pej1S92idxg
1783620703844712	w-rah2	itc:v3:AWLkkyTMk5PMmdAAAAAAQeq1bV17W4AAAAExAQ		item.comment	bn-rah2	{"body":"Starting work (w-rah2). Created workspace bn-rah2. Will build binary, run /tmp/repro_rah2.sh + control to reproduce, then implement guarded sibling replay in reconcile_epoch_with_branch and retire raw HEAD writes in sync_ff_paths_in_worktree + sync_target_worktree_to_epoch."}	blake3:VIwS1V8bueGZhW2ClbtighyWFyg7ivU8cQHlPhMi87s
1783620843030548	maw-dev/0	itc:v3:AWL_JPJM885kQAAAAAAAQf9Xq3vdoAAAAAEsIA		item.comment	bn-rah2	{"body":"Resuming in workspace bn-rah2. Root cause identified: reconcile_epoch_with_branch() calls sync_ff_paths_in_worktree() for all sibling workspaces unconditionally, which writes a raw OID to the worktree HEAD file. For workspaces with committed work, this orphans their commits — HEAD resets to the FF-absorbed branch tip while the committed work content stays in the worktree as uncommitted changes."}	blake3:_75c0tRZ_IGKYq2xtjRYp0SunyGeNGhExUJJ_cB95Lw
1783621155415336	w-rah2	itc:v3:AWLkkyTMk5PMmdAAAAAAQeq1bV17W4AAAAExAg		item.comment	bn-rah2	{"body":"Reproduced the bug against workspace binary. Root cause confirmed: reconcile_epoch_with_branch's FF-absorb treats EVERY non-default workspace (both merge source AND idle siblings) via sync_ff_paths_in_worktree, which raw-resets HEAD to the absorbed branch tip. For committed-ahead siblings this orphans the work commit (files left untracked). The merge's own AUTO-REBASE then skips them as 'dirty' (dirtied BY the absorb). Sources survive by luck (re-snapshot); non-source siblings orphan+go stale. Plan: (1) expose guarded maw-git set_head_detached; (2) classify each non-target sibling: UpToDate(skip) / HEAD==base_epoch (FF via guarded set_head) / committed-ahead+clean (guarded rebase_workspace_run replay) / committed-ahead+dirty (abort absorb -> diverged); rebases run BEFORE global epoch advance so a failure leaves no ref/HEAD changes; (3) retire both raw std::fs::write(HEAD) in sync_ff_paths_in_worktree + sync_target_worktree_to_epoch; (4) per-sibling NOTE lines + tests."}	blake3:t2vvDFoydaStzkk_01U2JkMITiE852iNSeXBKJeQXKM
1783621451398893	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyxQ		item.comment	bn-3rst	{"body":"Implemented: sync/rebase dirty-refusals now name the offending paths.\n\nFiles changed (workspace bn-3rst, commit e2aae38e):\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/checks.rs: added `dirty_status_entries` (extracted the status_head_to_worktree call from `workspace_has_uncommitted_changes`, which now just checks emptiness), `format_dirty_paths` (caps at 10 entries, one per line as \"  <letter> <path>\", then \"  ...and N more\"; empty slice -> \"\"), and `status_letter` (M/A/D/??/R). Updated the sync bail at the old checks.rs:194 site to splice in `format_dirty_paths(&dirty_entries)`.\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/rebase.rs: same treatment for the matching \"lost by rebase\" bail (was line ~337, same predicate/message shape as the sync refusal).\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/mod.rs: the soft \"auto-sync skipped, workspace dirty\" WARNING path (~line 879) also now prints the dirty paths, for consistency with the hard refusals.\n\nLeft untouched (per bone note \"if refusal propagates before JSON rendering, leave JSON alone\"): `ws sync --format json`'s `build_sync_json` calls `sync_worktree_to_epoch(...)?` — the dirty-refusal bail propagates as an `Err` out of `build_sync_json` before any `SyncJsonOutput` is constructed, so JSON is never rendered for this case; the improved plain-text error message is what the user/agent sees either way. No JSON schema change needed.\n\nadvance.rs was checked and does NOT share this predicate — dirty state there is handled via snapshot/replay, not refusal, so out of scope.\n\nTests added (crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/checks.rs, `mod tests`):\n- sync_refusal_names_dirty_paths: stale-free workspace with one modified tracked file (.gitignore) + one new file (scratch.txt) -> sync_worktree_to_epoch errors, message contains \"M .gitignore\" and \"A scratch.txt\". Note: status_head_to_worktree is HEAD-relative, so a new file surfaces as FileStatus::Added (\"A\"), not FileStatus::Untracked (\"??\") -- documented inline, matches a pre-existing dead-code note in init.rs about Untracked never being produced by this predicate today. format_dirty_paths still maps Untracked -> \"??\" for any future/other caller.\n- format_dirty_paths_lists_entries_under_cap: 5 entries, all 5 statuses, exact multi-line output assertion.\n- format_dirty_paths_truncates_over_cap: 13 entries -> 10 listed + \"...and 3 more\".\n- format_dirty_paths_empty_for_no_entries.\n\nVerification:\n- cargo fmt --check -p maw-cli: clean.\n- cargo clippy -p maw-cli --all-targets -- -D warnings: clean (fixed two nursery lints along the way: missing_const_for_fn on status_letter, needless_range_loop in the truncation test).\n- cargo test -p maw-cli --lib workspace::sync::: 52 passed, 0 failed.\n- maw exec bn-3rst -- just check: full suite green, grepped complete output for \"test result: FAILED\" and broader \"fail\" -- no genuine failures, only test names containing \"fail\" all ending \"... ok\".\n\nDeviations: extended the auto-sync WARNING path in sync/mod.rs in addition to the two hard bail! refusals named in the bone -- same predicate, same \"orphaned work vs junk\" rationale, small delta, kept in scope. No rebase.rs-specific integration test was added (checks.rs's sync_refusal_names_dirty_paths + the format_dirty_paths unit tests already cover the shared helper that rebase.rs's bail reuses verbatim); flagging in case a reviewer wants belt-and-suspenders coverage there too.\n\nCommitted only, NOT merged (per task instructions) -- workspace bn-3rst awaiting lead merge."}	blake3:zTFqExMnZpqA32vtpWuzsk3E5n4-qL1VPra1vHCFaq4
1783621525931363	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzBQ		item.move	bn-3rst	{"state":"done"}	blake3:cA-QVFSaDjTYkvFQX6Y5wi4v1XOFkGzUkHqrOvOGo2A
1783621953272913	maw-dev/0	itc:v3:AWL_JPJM885kQAAAAAAAQf9Xq3vdoAAAAAEsIQ		item.move	bn-rah2	{"state":"done"}	blake3:B_tzQmhhCR2ko7e82Nj8g2k6oK5euODFr627g3a7_qg
1783622382983977	w-rah2	itc:v3:AWLkkyTMk5PMmdAAAAAAQeq1bV17W4AAAAExAw		item.comment	bn-rah2	{"body":"DONE — fix implemented, verified, and (externally) landed in main as commit 68abe479.\n\nAPPROACH:\n- crates/maw-git/src/gix_repo.rs: added guarded pub fn set_head_detached (atomic HEAD write + reflog, no worktree touch) — the primitive that retires the raw std::fs::write(HEAD).\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/rebase.rs: added pub fn rebase_sibling_for_absorb wrapping rebase_workspace_run (print=false, mutate_worktree=true, acquire_lock=true, continue_past_worktree_failure=false) — exposes the guarded rebase to merge.rs.\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs reconcile_epoch_with_branch Safe arm: replaced the old 'reset every sibling HEAD' loop (and the incomplete sibling_head_safe_to_ff skip-guard) with per-sibling classification: UpToDate(skip) / FastForward{dirty} (HEAD==base_epoch: guarded FF materialize) / Replay (committed-ahead+clean: guarded rebase onto absorbed tip). committed-ahead+dirty -> bail_diverged BEFORE any mutation. Replays run BEFORE write_epoch_current so a failure leaves epoch untouched + already-replayed siblings coherent (never half-moved). Per-sibling NOTE lines + retained aggregate 'Absorbed N' line.\n- Retired BOTH raw std::fs::write(HEAD) writes (sync_ff_paths_in_worktree + sync_target_worktree_to_epoch) -> ws_repo.set_head_detached (bn-8flz invariant: no production HEAD movement outside guarded native primitives).\n\nREPRO before/after (/tmp/repro_rah2.sh):\n- BEFORE (pre-fix): wsb HEAD reset to absorbed branch tip; '?? crates/b_work.txt' untracked; ws list '(stale)'; 'maw ws sync wsb' -> Error: 'has uncommitted changes that would be lost by sync'.\n- AFTER (fixed): 'Absorbed 2 upstream commit(s)' + 'wsb: replayed 1 commit(s) onto absorbed epoch' + 'wsa: replayed 1 commit(s)...'; wsb HEAD = rebased descendant (6fb16ef); git status CLEAN; HEAD:crates/b_work.txt = workB (COMMITTED); reflog shows 'maw: set_head (rebase)'; ws list '(ready to merge)'; 'maw ws sync wsb' -> 'Workspace wsb is up to date.' Control (dirty-only sibling / no-absorb) intact.\n\nTESTS (tests/merge_ff_absorb.rs, all green): ff_absorb_replays_committed_ahead_sibling (HEAD rebased+contains work as COMMITTED, clean, sync=up-to-date, NOTE emitted), ff_absorb_preserves_dirty_only_sibling_edits (control), ff_absorb_blocks_on_committed_ahead_dirty_sibling (blocked, HEAD+epoch untouched), + reusable assert_sibling_work_preserved invariant helper. 37/37 in that file.\n\nGATES: cargo fmt --all --check clean, cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings clean, full 'just check' GREEN (69 test-result:ok, 0 FAILED, verified by grepping the complete log).\n\nNOTE: my workspace bn-rah2 was merged+destroyed by a concurrent orchestration process (MergeDestroy, 18:32Z) mid-'just check' — that first check aborted with a spurious 'maw binary not found' (workspace torn down under it), NOT a logic failure. Work is intact in main 68abe479; re-ran full 'just check' on main = green. Did not push/close the bone."}	blake3:gu57rtNXOKGd6Tvzy1YkzOScIJT2QlkIEwvjZF5o-zw
1783623018763271	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzRQ		item.comment	bn-rah2	{"body":"Lead review + verification complete on main (68abe479): design matches the decided fix (classification before mutation; committed-ahead+dirty blocks BEFORE any ref change; replays before epoch advance; both raw HEAD writes retired to guarded set_head_detached; per-sibling NOTEs). Independently verified: 37/37 merge_ff_absorb tests incl. 3 new; live repro — sibling work ends COMMITTED at rebased HEAD, tree clean, ws sync up-to-date, loud output. Full just check green (0 FAILED / 69 suites). Note: the workspace was merged by the auto-spawned maw-dev/0 dev loop rather than the lead; merged bytes verified identical to the worker's final state. Fix is on main, ships in the next pre-release."}	blake3:S164quS3bhth3GZgP4g3VjQVcMZjCwL6jgXDOAyEBPQ
