1783705643515996	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy9xQ		item.comment	bn-1m4d	{"body":"Lead triage (maw-dev, 2026-07-10): ALL FIVE ITEMS ACCEPTED. Item 1 -> bn-1lhb (post_sync hook in HooksConfig, results in ws list + merge summary + JSON; jj-model preserved: signal-only, never blocks). Item 2 -> bn-drk3 (middle path taken: ext-aware line-comment header prefixes, // for .rs etc., legacy # forms stay parseable everywhere - full sidecar move stays declined since the header is the bn-28d1 tripwire + bn-39i8 reconstruction source). Items 3+4 -> bn-20fp (merge JSON gap-fill incl. per-sibling rebase outcomes/conflicts/overlap/cwd_destroyed/invariant summary; one trailing json-hint line in text output; destroy-cwd warning becomes the tail-visible final line). Item 5 -> bn-auu5 (maw ws clean with destroy-grade recovery snapshot before any deletion, plus a definitive investigation of the info/exclude dirty-check complaint - suspicion: gix consults the wrong exclude file for LINKED WORKTREES, .git/info/exclude vs .git/worktrees/<n>/info/exclude, which would explain why the earlier repro on a plain repo passed). Also note: your report crossed with today's reliability drop on main - repo-level epoch lock, Prime-Invariant runtime auditor (INVARIANT proof line per merge), maw undo/ops log, maw fsck --repair, DST oracles for exactly the bn-rah2/bn-1xmk/bn-3uou classes. Ships in pre.12."}	blake3:8nuxJHCc_k9gJ0UpWSzTYXUUkywskZpzlluLHLaiWjg
