1783713697874024	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjBU		item.create	bn-1d22	{"description":"Found while gating maw-cli tests into just check (bn-1q7x): the flock-based lock unit tests (crates/maw-cli/src/epoch_lock.rs, workspace/sync/lock.rs) fail ~20-30% of the time under default cargo-test parallelism, 0% at --test-threads=1 (10+ clean full runs). Ruled out by the bn-1n2b worker: lock-path collision across tempdirs (LayoutFlavor::manifold_dir is root-scoped, no caching), per-test tempdir isolation bugs, subprocess integration flakiness (those are stable), and the POSIX-fcntl process-wide gotcha (fs4 uses BSD flock via rustix, fd-scoped). Root cause NOT identified. Current mitigation: just check runs cargo test -p maw-cli -- --test-threads=1 (~12s, documented in Justfile). Investigate properly: candidate theories include flock() inheritance across fork/exec in test helpers, shared /home/bob/.maw config reads, tempdir-on-same-fs contention, or a real race in the lock code itself that only tests expose. If it IS a real race, this is a reliability bug in the epoch lock, not a test bug — treat as such until proven otherwise.","kind":"bug","title":"flaky flock unit tests in epoch_lock.rs + sync/lock.rs under parallel cargo test (root cause unknown)"}	blake3:Oq1nwR3gbmZQ1_Q7K7KIPu6fdKwLLfRP0guL-KLlsuk
